description:
'''Manzanita y su Conjunto''' are a [[Peru]]vian band founded by guitarist Berardo "Manzanita" Hernández in 1969.
The band played an important role in the development of [[Peruvian cumbia]] as a genre distinct from its [[Cumbia (Colombia)|Colombian]] roots.{{r|cosmalon}}
''[[Songlines (magazine)|Songlines]]'' wrote that Manzanita's music "revolutionised the music scene in Peru and left an indelible mark on Latin American music as a whole."{{r|songlines-2024}}

Alongside Hernández on guitar, Manzanita y su Conjunto also included Héctor Mattos on congos, Antonio Medina on bongos, Ricardo Valles on [[timbales]], Enrique Ibérico on bass, and  Hernan Huamán on organ.{{r|klof}}
When Hernández died in 2007, his son took up leadership of the group.
